# Supabase — required for auth + multi-device sync. Without these the app
# runs in guest mode (IndexedDB only). See README → Supabase setup.
#
# Use the new "API keys" naming (rolled out late 2024/2025):
#   - Publishable key (prefix `sb_publishable_…`) goes in the browser.
#   - Secret key (prefix `sb_secret_…`) is server-only — bypasses RLS.
# Legacy `anon` JWTs still work if pasted into PUBLISHABLE_KEY; the SDK
# accepts either format.

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# Server-only — never expose. Required for the "Delete account" button in
# Settings (the /api/delete-account route uses it to call
# auth.admin.deleteUser). Leave unset to disable the button: the route
# returns 503 and the UI surfaces a "not configured" message instead.
# SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY=

# Server-only — never expose. Enables the AI meal planner: /api/meal-plan
# routes signed-in users' Auto-fill requests through Claude Haiku 4.5 for
# more coherent food combinations. Leave unset and Auto-fill silently
# falls back to the deterministic 3×3 Cramer solver. Get a key at
# https://console.anthropic.com → Settings → API keys.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Server-only — optional. A shared, cross-instance cache for Open Food Facts
# lookups (barcode + search), so a cold serverless instance is as fast as a
# warm one. Without these the app still works: every OFF lookup falls through
# to a direct fetch (fail-open) — just slower on a cold start, never broken.
# Provision from the Vercel Marketplace → Upstash Redis (both vars are injected
# together; rotating the token needs no redeploy). Use the https:// REST
# endpoint, not the redis:// connection string.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=

# ── Release social automation (publishing) ──────────────────────────────────
# Drafting + review at /admin/social needs NONE of the below; these only enable
# LIVE posting. Without a platform's vars, its action stays a manual "Mark
# posted" rather than a real "Publish". NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL must be set so the
# Instagram card URL is publicly fetchable.

# LinkedIn — post to a company Page via the Posts API (w_organization_social).
# CLIENT_ID + PRIMARY_CLIENT_SECRET are the OAuth app creds used to OBTAIN the
# token; ACCESS_TOKEN + ORG_ID are what actually post. Find the org id from your
# Page admin URL, and get a token via the OAuth flow or LinkedIn's token tool.
# LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID=
# LINKEDIN_PRIMARY_CLIENT_SECRET=
# LINKEDIN_PAGE_URL=
# LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# LINKEDIN_ORG_ID=

# X — post via API v2 (paid tier). OAuth 1.0a user context: the app's consumer
# key/secret plus the account's access token/secret (Developer Portal → Keys).
# X_API_KEY=
# X_API_SECRET=
# X_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# X_ACCESS_SECRET=

# Instagram — post via the Graph API. Needs an IG Business account linked to a
# Facebook Page: the IG user id + a long-lived Page token with
# instagram_content_publish.
# META_IG_USER_ID=
# META_ACCESS_TOKEN=
